HEADWORD: Rill
<hw>Rill</hw> <pr>(r⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LG.
<ets>rille</ets> a small channel or brook, a furrow, a chamfer, OE.
<ets>rigol</ets> a small brook, F. <ets>rigole</ets> a trench or furrow
for water, W. <ets>rhill</ets> a row, <ets>rhigol</ets> a little ditch.
⟦root⟧11.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A very small brook; a
streamlet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>See <er>Rille</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
